courses.subject: GE
courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B2, B4, Upper-Division B, C1, Lower-Division C Elective, D1, D2, Upper-Division D, Lower-Division E, F, and GE Elective. Upper-Division B and Upper-Division D should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). Upper Division C must be satisfied by taking a non-English course. Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR).

courses.subject: Free Elective
courses.customDesc:
Any Free Elective course can go here. Recommended: Foreign Language 101.

Majors must demonstrate intermediate-level proficiency in a foreign language. Any language classes needed before intermediate level will count as free electives. With approval, students can substitute for this requirement by demonstrating a comparable level of proficiency in a foreign language.

courses.subject: Elective
courses.customDesc: Any Elective (ENGL 300-level) course can go here. See catalog for Upper Division courses. English majors are encouraged to use their upper-division ENGL electives to pursue their interests, including literature, creative writing, linguistics, and/or rhetoric and writing. Minimum 12 units in 400-level literature within the 24 total units of 400-level courses.
